        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-28T00:58:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-28T00:58:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>247. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Mission Broadcasting Station</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d247fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 6, Folder 6. Secret; Operational Immediate; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Repeated to [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] and the Director of Central
                        Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-28T05:58:00+00:00">June 28, 1954,
                        0558Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>4459. For <persName corresp="#p_LPD1">Langevin</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CIG1">Cadick</persName>.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1">Arbenz</persName> is out but <persName
                            corresp="#p_DCCE1">Diaz</persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d247fn2">The <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>
                            believed that <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1">Diaz</persName> was a
                            “veteran trained Communist, graduate Commie military agent school
                            Prague, Czechoslovakia preparing Moscow activities throughout Latin
                            America.” (Telegram 4478 from <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                                >PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters to various Stations, June 28;
                            ibid.)</note> refuses to accept <persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                            >Calligeris</persName>’s terms. Only 500 regular army and 2500 untrained
                        reserves in <gloss target="#t_ADAM1">Adam</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Immediately inform public what has happened and that if cease and terms
                            <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 4362 (IN 22435)<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d247fn3">Dated June 26. (Ibid., Folder 5)</note> not complied
                        with immediately <gloss target="#t_SYNCARP1">SYNCARP</gloss> will launch all
                        out bombing attack and assault and destroy all those not joining
                        anti-Communist forces. Communism must go and <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1"
                            >Diaz</persName> must agree to terms or army of liberation will continue
                        its victorious march to <gloss target="#t_ADAM1">Adam</gloss> and fight
                        Communists to last one.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Appeal to people that Communist <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1"
                            >Arbenz</persName> has resigned, first victory won and everyone should
                        now join side of liberation movement for a greater <gloss
                            target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss>. The government is obviously
                        crumbling and further bloodshed futile. Prepare leaflets for troops in
                        field.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Tell <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1">Diaz</persName> bombings to start noon
                        28 June and will not stop until liberation army occupies palace or <persName
                            corresp="#p_DCCE1">Diaz</persName> agrees to terms announced.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Target but don’t announce for noon 28 June is Matamoros again and knock
                        out brief pilots from <persName corresp="#p_LPD1">Langevin</persName>’s
                        staff or [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>]. Put on maximum air
                        show. Strafe all <gloss target="#t_AA1">AA</gloss> batteries.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_SHERWOOD1">SHERWOOD</gloss> to keep steady strong appeal
                        that anti-Communists are victorious and <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1"
                            >Diaz</persName> must agree cease fire before hundreds of innocent army
                        men die in lost cause. Only way to stop bloodshed is to drive communism out.
                        No other solution acceptable.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
